Frank LEWIS, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 7262. Feb. 21, 1934. Wm. C. Pierce and W. K. Zewadski, both of Tampa, Fla., for appellant. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. John W. Holland, U. S. Atty., of Jacksonville Fla.

^Before BRYAN, SIBLEY, and WALK-R, Circuit u ges.

PER CURIAM.

This is an appeal from a judgment of eon-vietion for violations of the National Prohibition Act (2-7 USCA). Upon the authority of United States v. Chambers, 54 S. Ct. 434, 78 L. Ed.- (opinion filed February 5; 1934), the judgment is reversed and annulled,
